emakes, and stories about how cinema contributed to the soundtrack of people’s lives. Ultimately, Film, Music, Memory demonstrates that music has transformed not only what we remember about the cinematic experience, but also how we relate to memory itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aMemory in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture musicxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aBernard Stiegler.  aMiriam Hansen.  aWalter Benjamin.  acinematic experience.  afilm.  amemory.  amusic.  aoptical unconscious.  aoptical-acoustic unconscious.  atertiary memory.1 aGunning, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226649894423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226649894/original  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPKb2019